info.title: TWIN - Test Endpoints
info.description: REST API for TWIN - Test Endpoints.

tags.name: Document Management
tags.description: Endpoints which are modelled to access a document management contract.

post.summary: Store a document in an auditable item graph vertex and add its content to blob storage.

parameters.name: auditableItemGraphId
parameters.description: The id of the auditable item graph vertex to store the document on.

requestBody.description: Request to set a document in an auditable item graph vertex.

201.description: The rest request ended in created response.

400.description: The server cannot process the request, see the content for more details.

401.description: You are not authorized to use the API or no credentials were supplied, see the content for more details.

500.description: The server has encountered a situation it does not know how to handle, see the content for more details.

get.summary: Query the items from an auditable item graph vertex

parameters.name: auditableItemGraphId
parameters.description: The id of the auditable item graph vertex which contains the documents.

parameters.name: documentCodes
parameters.description: List of comma separated document codes to filter the query.

parameters.name: includeRemoved
parameters.description: Include deleted documents in the response.

parameters.name: includeMostRecentRevisions
parameters.description: Include the most recent 5 revisions, use the individual get to retrieve more.

parameters.name: cursor
parameters.description: The cursor to get the next chunk of documents.

200.description: Response to query the documents from an auditable item graph vertex.

400.description: The server cannot process the request, see the content for more details.

401.description: You are not authorized to use the API or no credentials were supplied, see the content for more details.

500.description: The server has encountered a situation it does not know how to handle, see the content for more details.

get.summary: Get the data for a document from document management

parameters.name: auditableItemGraphId
parameters.description: The id of the auditable item graph vertex to store the document on.

parameters.name: documentId
parameters.description: The full id of the document to get.

parameters.name: includeBlobStorageMetadata
parameters.description: Include the blob storage metadata in the response.

parameters.name: includeBlobStorageData
parameters.description: Include the blob storage data in the response.

parameters.name: includeAttestation
parameters.description: Include the attestation information in the response.

parameters.name: includeRemoved
parameters.description: Include deleted documents in the response.

parameters.name: maxRevisionCount
parameters.description: Max number of revisions to return.

parameters.name: revisionCursor
parameters.description: The cursor to get the next chunk of revisions.

200.description: Response to get a document and optionally revisions from an auditable item graph vertex.

400.description: The server cannot process the request, see the content for more details.

401.description: You are not authorized to use the API or no credentials were supplied, see the content for more details.

404.description: The resource you tried to access does not exist, see the content for more details.

500.description: The server has encountered a situation it does not know how to handle, see the content for more details.

delete.summary: Remove an document from an auditable item graph vertex

parameters.name: auditableItemGraphId
parameters.description: The id of the auditable item graph vertex to remove the document from.

parameters.name: documentId
parameters.description: The full id of the document to remove.

parameters.name: removeAllRevisions
parameters.description: Flag to remove all revisions of the document.

204.description: The rest request ended in success with no data.

400.description: The server cannot process the request, see the content for more details.

401.description: You are not authorized to use the API or no credentials were supplied, see the content for more details.

404.description: The resource you tried to access does not exist, see the content for more details.

500.description: The server has encountered a situation it does not know how to handle, see the content for more details.

id.description: The unique identifier of the attestation.

dateCreated.description: Created date/time of the attestation in ISO format.

dateTransferred.description: Transferred date/time of the attestation in ISO format, can be blank if holder identity is owner.

holderIdentity.description: The identity of the current holder, can be undefined if owner is still the holder.

verified.description: Whether the attestation has been verified.

AttestationInformation.description: Interface describing the collated attestation information.

dateCreated.description: The date/time when the entry was created.

dateModified.description: The date/time when the entry was modified.

blobSize.description: The size of the data in the blob.

blobHash.description: The hash of the data in the blob.

encodingFormat.description: The mime type for the blob.

blob.description: The blob in base64 format, included if the includeContent flag was set in the request.

BlobStorageEntry.description: Interface describing a blob storage entry.

id.description: The full id of the document.

documentIdFormat.description: The format of the document id.

documentRevision.description: The revision of the document as a 0 based index.

blobStorageId.description: The blob storage id for the document.

blobHash.description: The hash of the blob data.

attestationId.description: The attestation for the document if one was created.

dateCreated.description: The date/time of when the document was created.

dateModified.description: The date/time of when the document was modified.

dateDeleted.description: The date/time of when the document was deleted, as we never actually remove items.

nodeIdentity.description: The node which added the document to the graph.

userIdentity.description: The user who added the document to the graph.

revisions.description: The previous revisions of the document.

revisionCursor.description: The cursor to get the next chunk of revisions.

cursor.description: The cursor to get the next chunk of documents.

DocumentList.description: Interface describing a document entry list.

documentIdFormat.description: The format of the document identifier.

blob.description: The data to create the document with, in base64.

createAttestation.description: Flag to create an attestation for the document, defaults to false

properties.description: Any additional information for the error.

stack.description: The stack trace for the error.

JsonLdContextDefinition.description: A context definition defines a local context in a node object.

JsonLdContextDefinitionElement.description: A context definition element is used to define the types of a context definition.

JsonLdContextDefinitionRoot.description: A context definition root is used to define the root of a context definition.

JsonLdExpandedTermDefinition.description: An expanded term definition is used to describe the mapping between a term and its expanded identifier, as well as other properties of the value associated with the term when it is used as key in a node object.

JsonLdGraphObject.description: A graph object represents a named graph, which MAY include an explicit graph name.

JsonLdIdMap.description: An id map is used to associate an IRI with a value that allows easy programmatic access.

JsonLdIncludedBlock.description: An included block is used to provide a set of node objects.

JsonLdIndexMap.description: An index map allows keys that have no semantic meaning, but should be preserved regardless, to be used in JSON-LD documents.

JsonLdIndexMapItem.description: The items that can be stored in an index map.

JsonLdKeyword.description: A list of keywords and their types. Only used for internal reference; not an actual interface. Not for export.

JsonLdLanguageMap.description: A language map is used to associate a language with a value in a way that allows easy programmatic access.

JsonLdListObject.description: A list represents an ordered set of values.

JsonLdListOrSetItem.description: A list or set item can be a null, boolean, number, string, node object, or value object.

JsonLdNodeObject.description: A node object represents zero or more properties of a node in the graph serialized by the JSON-LD document.

JsonLdNodePrimitive.description: A node primitive is a JSON-LD value which is not one of the defined NodeObject properties.

JsonLdSetObject.description: A set represents an unordered set of values.

JsonLdTypeMap.description: A type map is used to associate an IRI with a value that allows easy programmatic access.

JsonLdValueObject.description: A value object is used to explicitly associate a type or a language with a value to create a typed value or a language-tagged string and possibly associate a base direction.

notFoundId.description: The id if the item that was not found.

properties.description: Any additional information for the error.

stack.description: The stack trace for the error.

NotFoundResponse.description: The body which contains the error.
